        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hi,\n  I'm basically working on Magento that uses the Zend framework. In the version of Magento that uses Zend version 1.5.1, the Indian currency (INR) is correctly displayed as Rs. However, when I moved to a new version of Magento that uses Zend 1.7.2, the currency appears as Rp (instead of Rs.).\nWhile searching for this I came across ZF-6208 wherein there is a note that : \nFor the locale en_IN, the currency INR is defined with the currency sign \"Rp\".\nAny help in expediting a fix for this would be greatly appreciated.\nThanks."
        },
