                    "created": "2009-05-26T11:20:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-26T11:20:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32437",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=paramz74",
                        "name": "paramz74",
                        "displayName": "Param",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Thomas,\n   Thanks for the note and the link to unicode.org. The main issue is that the currency sign for the INR is Rs and so I created a bug at the unicode site (bug id 2239). They have apparently fixed it in the latest 1.7.1 release. \nYou can see the diff here : http:\/\/www.unicode.org\/cgi-bin\/bugdiffs.pl?id=2239&ignore_attic=on \nIs there a way to let me know when you will be releasing with 1.7.1? Is that even necessary or can I just use the latest xml files?\nThanks a lot.\n\nCheers\n--Param",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=paramz74",
                        "name": "paramz74",
                        "displayName": "Param",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-07T01:07:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-07T01:07:52.000+0000"
                }
            ]
